body_html: Thanks @kwotsin ! First off, you probably want to pay heed to the warning and see if your problem disappears after that. Then, I would suggest using tf.Print the tf debugger, or asking for parts of the graph that are earlier than that. If that doesn't work for you, please ask piecemeal questions on stackoverflow, where we monitor all questions with the tag "tensorflow".

body: Thanks @kwotsin ! First off, you probably want to pay heed to the warning and see if your problem disappears after that. Then, I would suggest using `tf.Print` the tf debugger, or asking for parts of the graph that are earlier than that. If that doesn't work for you, please ask piecemeal questions on stackoverflow, where we monitor all questions with the tag "tensorflow".
